modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to byte streams, including composition of streams and transformation of data. Operates on byte buffers, input and output channels, and effectful operations compatible with OCaml 5's scheduler. Enables building efficient, modular I/O pipelines for network communication, file processing, and data serialization.

Provides functions to create compressed or decompressed input and output streams, with optional buffering. Operates on input and output buffers (`Iostream.In_buf.t`, `Iostream.Out_buf.t`) to handle data compression and decompression using Zlib. Enables writing compressed data to a file or network stream or reading and decompressing data from an input source.
